<html>
  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> BLOATING_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles.css" id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css" id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet"
      title="dark">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body>
    <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="git General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: BLOATING</h3>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>: Character</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Sensation of Bloating/Fullness:</b> <span class="git">IBS,
                Functional Dyspepsia, Food Intolerance</span></li>
            <li><b>Visible Abdominal Distension:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="git emergency">Constipation, Bowel Obstruction</li>
                <li class="cvs git emergency">Ascites (fluid from liver/heart
                  failure, malignancy)</li>
                <li class="gynob oncology">Large ovarian cyst or tumor</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li>Is it more of a gassy feeling, or a feeling of heaviness?</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When you say 'bloating', is it a feeling of
          fullness and pressure, or do you notice your tummy is visibly swollen
          (distended)?"</span></div>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site of Discomfort</span>
          <ul>
            <li>GENERALIZED: <span class="git">IBS, constipation, ascites</span></li>
            <li>UPPER ABDOMEN: <span class="git">Functional Dyspepsia,
                Gastroparesis, H. pylori</span></li>
            <li>LOWER ABDOMEN: <span class="gynob">Gynaecological causes
                (fibroids, ovarian cysts)</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is the bloating felt all over your abdomen, or is
          it worse in a particular area?"</span></div>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
          <ul>
            <li>ACUTE: <span class="git emergency">Bowel Obstruction</span>, <span
                class="infectious">Gastroenteritis</span></li>
            <li>CHRONIC / RECURRENT: <span class="git">IBS</span>, <span class="git">Food
                Intolerance</span>, <span class="gynob">Ovarian issues</span></li>
            <li class="oncology gynob emergency">Persistent, daily bloating for
              &gt; 2 weeks in a woman &gt; 50 is a red flag for ovarian cancer.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When did the bloating start? Did it come on
          suddenly, or has it been a gradual problem?"</span></div>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"When you get a bout of bloating, how long does it
          typically last?"</span></div>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>: Aggravating &amp;
            Relieving Factors</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>AGGRAVATING:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="git">After eating any meal (Dyspepsia, Gastroparesis)</li>
                <li class="git">Specific foods (e.g., dairy, wheat, high-FODMAP
                  foods)</li>
                <li class="psychiatric">Stress or anxiety</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>RELIEVING:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="git">Passing gas or having a bowel movement (classic
                  for IBS)</li>
                <li class="git">Fasting / Not eating</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"What seems to bring it on or make it worse? Does
          anything help to relieve it?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Radiation (of Pain)</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"If you have any pain with the bloating, does it
          travel anywhere?"</span></div>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>: Associated Symptoms</span>
          <ul>
            <li><b>GASTROINTESTINAL CLUES:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="git">Change in Bowel Habit (Diarrhea, Constipation,
                  or Alternating) -&gt; <b class="git">IBS</b></li>
                <li class="git">Abdominal Pain (relieved by defecation?)</li>
                <li class="git">Nausea, heartburn, or early satiety</li>
                <li class="git"><b>Leg swelling in<br>
                  </b></li>
                <li class="git">Liver fail - ascites</li>
                <li class="git">Renal - ascites</li>
                <li class="git">heart failure -ascites</li>
                <li class="git">Excessive flatulence or belching</li>
                <li class="git">Steatorrhea (greasy stools) -&gt; <b class="git">Malabsorption</b></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>GYNAECOLOGICAL CLUES:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="gynob">Pelvic pain</li>
                <li class="gynob">Abnormal vaginal bleeding (intermenstrual,
                  postmenopausal)</li>
                <li class="gynob">Pain during intercourse (dyspareunia)</li>
                <li class="gynob">Bloating related to menstrual cycle</li>
              </ul>
            </li>
            <li><b>SYSTEMIC / ALARM SYMPTOMS:</b>
              <ul>
                <li class="oncology">Unexplained weight loss</li>
                <li class="hematology">Symptoms of anemia (fatigue, shortness of
                  breath)</li>
                <li class="cvs">Ankle swelling (edema) -&gt; <b class="cvs">Ascites
                    (Heart/Liver failure)</b></li>
                <li class="respiratory">Shortness of breath -&gt; <b class="respiratory">Ascites</b></li>
              </ul>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Along with the bloating, have you had any change
          in your bowel habits, pain, or any other symptoms?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Progression</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Has the bloating been getting progressively worse
          over time?"</span></div>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
          <ul>
            <li>Worse as the day progresses -&gt; <b class="git">Classic for
                IBS/Functional Bloating</b></li>
            <li>Constant and unremitting -&gt; <b class="cvs git gynob emergency">More
                concerning for ascites or a mass</b></li>
            <li>Related to menstrual cycle -&gt; <b class="gynob">Hormonal/Gynaecological
                cause</b></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"Is there a pattern to the bloating? For example,
          is it better in the morning and worse by the end of the day?"</span></div>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect on Life</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"How has this been affecting you? Does it affect
          what you wear, your diet, or your social life?"</span></div>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red Flags</span>
          <ul>
            <li class="oncology">Unexplained weight loss</li>
            <li class="git hematology">Rectal bleeding or signs of anemia</li>
            <li class="oncology git">New onset of symptoms in a person &gt; 50
              years old</li>
            <li class="gynob oncology emergency"><b>Persistent or frequent
                bloating (most days) in a woman, especially &gt; 50</b> (Ovarian
              Cancer)</li>
            <li class="git emergency">Persistent vomiting or difficulty
              swallowing (dysphagia)</li>
            <li class="cvs git">Palpable abdominal or pelvic mass</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific questions to make
          sure we're not missing anything serious."</span></div>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <div class="point">
        <div class="point-content">
          <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity / Bother Scale</span>
        </div>
        <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how much does this bloating
          bother you?"</span></div>
    </div>
    <script src="harsha_iframe_youtube_player.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height_mothership.js"></script>
    <script src="Iframe_height.js"></script>
